cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper deals with rateless codes for streaming, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of different encoding and decoding schemes for different users also involves data structures (cs.DS) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the optimization of the code degree distribution can be seen as a multimedia optimization problem (cs.MM).
